slide.paragraphs:
Given an integral domain $R$ (commutative, with $1 
eq 0$). We consider the set: $R 	imes R_{
eq 0} := \{(a, b) : a, b \in R, b
eq 0\}$. We define a relation $\equiv$ on $R 	imes R_{
eq 0}$ as follows: \[ (a, b) \equiv (c, d) 	ext{ if } ad = bc. \]

